race.comment: JUST ALBERT (1) is back in Darwin after one start in Victoria, where he just missed at Tatura 25 days ago first-up. That reads well for this, and he can win if presented on song. MLINZI (5) wound up strongly to finish a head adrift over 1100m. Sure to go well again. Carries 3kg less with the claimer books and should enjoy the longer sprint. PATYEP (3) went close to shedding the tag in the same race. Made sharp improvement in that and it's hard to risk the Clarke yard. JUELENE (4) has had plenty of tries but her effort two back over shorter would have her around the mark. SASS (7) is ex-NSW and freshened but might need this.
